                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91293/165: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-19T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 19, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 20–10:53 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>595. Your telegram No. 235, July 18, 1 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Abend’s transfer to Shanghai was made known to the Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs recently at a luncheon given by him to the local representatives of
                        the foreign press. Almost immediately thereafter he had Abend sought out by
                        Kwangson Young, head of the information and publicity department of the
                        Nanking Government, who, after an attempt to force Abend into revealing his
                        confidential sources of information, assumed a very friendly tone and
                        offered to be of all possible assistance to him and to put him in touch with
                        news sources in Shanghai.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>It is my hope that the campaign against Abend will be dropped for the time
                        being at any rate. I would therefore suggest that I be authorized to
                        withhold reply to Wang’s note of June 17th unless he should again raise the
                        question.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
